{{See also|1934 in art}}

The year 1934 was marked by many events that left an imprint on the history of [[Soviet]] and [[Russia]]n Fine Arts.

==Events==
* Exhibition named <U+00AB>Women in Socialist construction<U+00BB> was opened in March in the [[Russian museum]] in Leningrad. The participants were [[Isaak Brodsky]], [[Piotr Buchkin]], [[Kazimir Malevich]], [[Victoria Belakovskaya]], [[Alexander Lubimov]], [[Alexander Samokhvalov]], [[Vladimir Malagis]], [[Yaroslav Nikolaev]], [[Konstantin Rudakov]], and other contemporary soviet artists<ref>''<U+0412><U+044B><U+0441><U+0442><U+0430><U+0432><U+043A><U+0430> <U+00AB><U+0416><U+0435><U+043D><U+0449><U+0438><U+043D><U+0430> <U+0432> <U+0441><U+043E><U+0446><U+0438><U+0430><U+043B><U+0438><U+0441><U+0442><U+0438><U+0447><U+0435><U+0441><U+043A><U+043E><U+043C> <U+0441><U+0442><U+0440><U+043E><U+0438><U+0442><U+0435><U+043B><U+044C><U+0441><U+0442><U+0432><U+0435><U+00BB>. <U+0416><U+0438><U+0432><U+043E><U+043F><U+0438><U+0441><U+044C>, <U+0441><U+043A><U+0443><U+043B><U+044C><U+043F><U+0442><U+0443><U+0440><U+0430>, <U+0433><U+0440><U+0430><U+0444><U+0438><U+043A><U+0430>''. <U+041B>., <U+0413><U+0420><U+041C>, 1934.</ref>.

* [[Isaak Brodsky]], a pupil of [[Ilya Repin]], has been appointed director of the All-Russian Academy of Arts and the [[Repin Institute of Arts|Leningrad Institute of Painting, Sculpture and Architecture]] (since 1944 named after Ilya Repin).

* The Secondary Art School was created under the [[Repin Institute of Arts|Leningrad Institute of Painting, Sculpture and Architecture]].

* Retrospective Exhibition of works by Honored Artist of the RSFSR [[Isaak Brodsky]] was opened in Moscow and Leningrad.

* Exhibition named <U+00AB>Leningrad in the image of contemporary artists<U+00BB> was opened in November in Leningrad. The participants were [[Anna Ostroumova-Lebedeva]], [[Vladimir Konashevich]], [[Elizaveta Kruglikova]], [[Victor Proshkin]], [[Vasily Vikulov]], and other contemporary Leningrad artists<ref>''Sergei V. Ivanov. Unknown Socialist Realism. The Leningrad School.'' Saint-Petersburg, NP-Print Edition, 2007. P.383.</ref>.

==Births==
* [[January 10]] <U+2014> [[Olga Yefimova]] ({{lang-ru|<U+0415><U+0444><U+0438><U+043C><U+043E><U+0432><U+0430> <U+041E><U+043B><U+044C><U+0433><U+0430> <U+0410><U+043B><U+0435><U+043A><U+0441><U+0430><U+043D><U+0434><U+0440><U+043E><U+0432><U+043D><U+0430>}}), Russian Soviet painter (d. [[1994 in art|1994]]).


== Deaths ==
* [[July 15]] <U+2014> [[Antonina Rzhevskaya]] ({{lang-ru|<U+0420><U+0436><U+0435><U+0432><U+0441><U+043A><U+0430><U+044F> <U+0410><U+043D><U+0442><U+043E><U+043D><U+0438><U+043D><U+0430> <U+041B><U+0435><U+043E><U+043D><U+0430><U+0440><U+0434><U+043E><U+0432><U+043D><U+0430>}}), [[Russia]]n painter (b. [[1861 in art|1861]]).
* [[October 14]] <U+2014> [[Mikhail Matyushin]] ({{lang-ru|<U+041C><U+0430><U+0442><U+044E><U+0448><U+0438><U+043D> <U+041C><U+0438><U+0445><U+0430><U+0438><U+043B> <U+0412><U+0430><U+0441><U+0438><U+043B><U+044C><U+0435><U+0432><U+0438><U+0447>}}), [[Russia]]n artist and art educator (b. [1861 in art|1861]]).
* [[November 27]] <U+2014> [[Mitrofan Grekov]] ({{lang-ru|<U+0413><U+0440><U+0435><U+043A><U+043E><U+0432> <U+041C><U+0438><U+0442><U+0440><U+043E><U+0444><U+0430><U+043D> <U+0411><U+043E><U+0440><U+0438><U+0441><U+043E><U+0432><U+0438><U+0447>}}), [[Russia]]n and Soviet battle painter (b. [[1882 in art|1882]])

